                <note type="article">
                    <p xml:id='OTPS32172228P0'>Located in Grayson County, Collinsville was founded in the late 1850s under the name Springville. In the 1860s the area was renamed Toadsuck. By 1877, the town was known as Collinsville, but the name was not officially changed until the town was incorporated in the 1890s. (David Minor, "Collinsville, TX," Texas State Historical Association; B. F. Blanton to the Sheriff of Carroll County, Mississippi, Civil War &amp; Reconstruction Governors of Mississippi, <id>mdah_807-1010-09-21</id>)
