<p corresp='TTP34242066P1' xml:id='OTP34242066P1'><rs ref='#S32174861'>Grayson Co, Texas</rs><lb/>
May 29<add place='above'><hi rend='underline'>th</hi></add><sub>"</sub> 1877
</p>

<p corresp='TTP34242066P2' xml:id='OTP34242066P2'>To the <rs ref='#S95578'>Sherriff</rs> of <rs ref='#S63223'>Carroll County Miss</rs>,
</p>

<p corresp='TTP34242066P3' xml:id='OTP34242066P3'>Sir
</p>

<p corresp='TTP34242066P4' xml:id='OTP34242066P4'>I wrote you a letter yestidday in relation to a man <del rend='overstrike'>killing</del> <rs ref='#S63926'>killing</rs> his step Father his name is <rs ref='#S32172229'>Randle</rs> in the place of <rs ref='#S32172230'>Finly</rs> &amp; his step Fathers name is <rs ref='#S32172232'>Bennett</rs>. if the circumstance is true &amp; ther is any <rs ref='#S32065746'>reward</rs> for him give me the full particulars of the affair and send
</p>


        </div>
        <pb xml:id="F34242067" n="2" facs="https://cdm17313.contentdm.oclc.org/iiif/2/mdah:44166/full/full/0/default.jpg"/>
        <div xml:id="OTP34242067">
        <fw type="pageNum">Page 2</fw>
          <p corresp='TTP34242067P0' xml:id='OTP34242067P0'>me the official papers at once
</p>

<p corresp='TTP34242067P1' xml:id='OTP34242067P1'>yours &amp;c.
</p>

<p corresp='TTP34242067P2' xml:id='OTP34242067P2'><rs ref='#S32172227'>B. F. Blanton</rs>
</p>

<p corresp='TTP34242067P3' xml:id='OTP34242067P3'>address<lb/>
<rs ref='#S32172228'>Collinsville<lb/>
Grayson County<lb/>
Texas</rs>
</p>


        </div>
